1
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:41,567
<i> You're all the same.</i>

2
00:00:41,700 --> 00:00:44,767
<i>You're no different
from my father.</i>

3
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:47,367
<i>Aren't you like that,
too, Joel?</i>

4
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:51,300
<i> Not all men just suddenly...</i>

5
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:52,800
<i> I'm leaving.</i>

6
00:00:52,933 --> 00:00:54,567
<i> I'm going to the party.</i>

7
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:56,033
<i>What are you
planning to do there?</i>

8
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:58,600
<i>- I will ruin the party!
- No, no, no!</i>

9
00:00:58,733 --> 00:01:01,167
<i>Dad, are you really not coming?</i>

10
00:01:01,300 --> 00:01:03,000
<i>No, dear.
Just go with your mom.</i>

11
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:05,300
<i> Tetay? I missed you!</i>

12
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:13,733
<i> Surprise!</i>

13
00:01:13,867 --> 00:01:15,733
<i>- Dad!
- Happy birthday, sweetie.</i>

14
00:01:19,300 --> 00:01:20,233
<i> Auntie Coleen?</i>

15
00:01:20,367 --> 00:01:21,567
<i> Why are you crying?</i>

16
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:25,200
<i>I wish everyone had a dad who
danced with them at their debut.</i>

17
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:26,600
<i> Coleen.</i>

18
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:28,467
<i>Coleen, dance
with Dad tonight.</i>

19
00:01:36,700 --> 00:01:38,300
<i> In my case with Manuel,</i>

20
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:42,000
<i>I hope we don't lose the trust
we have in each other</i>

21
00:01:42,167 --> 00:01:43,233
<i> as friends.</i>

22
00:01:43,367 --> 00:01:44,600
<i> Friends...</i>

23
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,367
<i>but living
under the same roof.</i>

24
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,433
<i>- Can you please stop?
- Hey!</i>

25
00:01:51,567 --> 00:01:52,967
<i>- Just leave already!
- I won't!</i>

26
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,667
<i>- Let go of me!
- Hazel, just go home!</i>

27
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,167
<i>- No! Manuel!
- Hazel!</i>

28
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:15,800
- How dare you!
- Mom, stop it! Please!

29
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:18,033
Do you know what someone
like you deserves, Felma?

30
00:02:18,167 --> 00:02:19,600
To be crippled,

31
00:02:19,733 --> 00:02:22,367
so you can never go near
my husband and child again.

32
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:23,533
Do you understand me?

33
00:02:24,933 --> 00:02:28,300
- No, Mom!
- Hazel, please, that's enough.

34
00:02:28,433 --> 00:02:30,900
Jessica's already embarrassed,
please

35
00:02:31,033 --> 00:02:32,567
Hazel, can you
please just leave?

36
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:33,700
No!

37
00:02:35,133 --> 00:02:37,200
I'm Jessica's mother.

38
00:02:37,333 --> 00:02:39,300
I have every right to be here.

39
00:02:39,433 --> 00:02:40,733
My child, sweetie.

40
00:02:40,867 --> 00:02:43,533
It should be me
giving this to you.

41
00:02:43,667 --> 00:02:45,367
Hello, police station?

42
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:46,500
Please come right now.

43
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:48,367
I've been calling
for a while!

44
00:02:48,533 --> 00:02:51,333
Yes, yes.
Tala Diwa, that's right.

45
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,500
It should be me giving this

46
00:02:52,633 --> 00:02:53,500
- to you.
- Mom, stop, please!

47
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:55,200
Because I'm your mother!

48
00:02:55,333 --> 00:02:56,700
Not her. Not that woman.

49
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:57,733
Not that Felma!

50
00:02:57,867 --> 00:02:58,767
It should be me

51
00:02:58,900 --> 00:02:59,767
- giving this to you.
- Mom, stop.

52
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:01,933
Mom! Mom, stop!

53
00:03:02,067 --> 00:03:03,700
It should be me, sweetie.

54
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:15,300
Mom.

55
00:03:17,200 --> 00:03:18,467
Mom.

56
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,467
I'm right here, Andrea.

57
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,467
Okay? I'm right here.

58
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,633
Mom.

59
00:03:26,167 --> 00:03:28,533
I don't want you
to get hurt, Mom.

60
00:03:30,167 --> 00:03:32,900
I don't want you to get hurt.

61
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Mom.

62
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,433
I'm just right here.

63
00:04:00,733 --> 00:04:02,667
You really have
no shame, Felma!

64
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,233
I won't let you completely
destroy my family!

65
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:07,867
- No! I won't allow it!
- What?

66
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,167
You can't!

67
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,767
- I won't allow it!
- What?

68
00:04:11,900 --> 00:04:13,433
I'll fight her!

69
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:14,667
Felma, don't stoop
to her level!

70
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,800
No!

71
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:18,667
Let me go! No!

72
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,100
- That's enough!
- Felm should...

73
00:04:20,233 --> 00:04:21,100
What?

74
00:04:21,233 --> 00:04:23,100
- Felma!
- Jessica...

75
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:24,900
Let go of me!

76
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,133
Jessica!

77
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:32,533
Jessica!

78
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:48,500
Jessica!

79
00:04:48,633 --> 00:04:51,967
Jessica!

80
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,533
Jessica, dear!
Wake up!

81
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:55,167
Jessica!
I'm sorry, dear!

82
00:04:55,300 --> 00:04:56,700
Call an ambulance!

83
00:04:56,833 --> 00:05:00,133
Call an ambulance! Dear!

84
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,167
Jessica!

85
00:05:01,300 --> 00:05:03,000
Jessica, dear!

86
00:05:03,133 --> 00:05:04,533
That way!

87
00:05:04,667 --> 00:05:06,867
- I'm sorry, dear. I'm sorry.
- The girl wearing white.

88
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:08,800
I didn't mean to. Sorry. Help!

89
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:12,367
Please help us! Please help us!

90
00:05:12,500 --> 00:05:16,567
Let's bring her
to the hospital!

91
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,100
Manuel.

92
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:20,867
Felma, Abel, go
with the ambulance.

93
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:23,700
Manuel and the rest of
us will follow, okay?

94
00:05:23,833 --> 00:05:25,000
I'm coming to the hospital.

95
00:05:25,133 --> 00:05:26,600
You're not coming with us!

96
00:05:26,733 --> 00:05:27,633
No.

97
00:05:27,767 --> 00:05:28,833
My daughter
doesn't need you!

98
00:05:28,967 --> 00:05:30,067
She needs us!

99
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:32,967
Manuel, no.

100
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,533
I'm Jessica's mother.

101
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,633
I'm coming with her.

102
00:05:35,767 --> 00:05:36,800
She needs me!

103
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,133
- Sir! Sir, that's her!
- Where?

104
00:05:38,267 --> 00:05:39,633
The one in red!

105
00:05:39,767 --> 00:05:41,733
- That's her! Arrest her!
- I'm coming...

106
00:05:41,867 --> 00:05:42,867
No!

107
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:43,833
That's the one we're filing
a complaint against.

108
00:05:43,967 --> 00:05:44,767
Felma! Where do you think
you're going?

109
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:46,300
- It's your fault...
- Ma'am, you need

110
00:05:46,433 --> 00:05:47,633
- to come with us.
- No, no!

111
00:05:47,767 --> 00:05:49,367
No! No! No!

112
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:51,300
Let go of me! My daughter
is in the hospital.

113
00:05:51,433 --> 00:05:54,500
Let go of me!

114
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:57,100
- Let's go!
- I need to be in the hospital!

115
00:06:03,567 --> 00:06:04,633
What happened
to you, sweetie?

116
00:06:05,667 --> 00:06:07,400
Why didn't you ask me
to pick you up?

117
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,400
Why, sweetie?

118
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:13,333
It's because of Miss Hazel, Dad.

119
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:16,333
She went
to Auntie Jessica's party,

120
00:06:16,467 --> 00:06:18,200
and then she lost it.

121
00:06:18,333 --> 00:06:21,100
She even went
after Mommy Pretty.

122
00:06:21,233 --> 00:06:22,533
What?

123
00:06:22,667 --> 00:06:23,767
She went after her.

124
00:06:23,900 --> 00:06:25,567
Did she hurt Mom?

125
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,200
We don't know, Jeff.

126
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:30,033
I panicked. That's why
I brought Tetay home.

127
00:06:31,667 --> 00:06:32,800
Hush now, sweetie. It's okay.

128
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:35,700
Dad!

129
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,100
Hush now.

130
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:15,900
Felma.

131
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:19,567
Felma, what did
the doctor say?

132
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:20,867
There's no news yet.

133
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:25,033
They took Jessica to the CT scan
room once she was stabilized.

134
00:07:28,367 --> 00:07:30,867
<i> Help us!</i>

135
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,533
<i> Help!</i>

136
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:34,100
<i>My child is having
an asthma attack.</i>

137
00:07:34,233 --> 00:07:34,867
<i> She can't breathe!</i>

138
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,100
<i> This way, please.</i>

139
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:53,767
Let me go!

140
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,500
Why are you locking me up?

141
00:07:55,633 --> 00:07:56,833
My child's in
the hospital!

142
00:07:56,967 --> 00:07:58,267
Take me there!

143
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,300
My child needs me!

144
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:02,467
- Get inside.
- Let me go!

145
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,300
Calm down, Ma'am.
If you don't stop,

146
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:06,967
we'll press charges
for direct assault.

147
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:09,200
I'll press charges
for police brutality!

148
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:11,400
We've been exercising
maximum tolerance with you

149
00:08:11,533 --> 00:08:12,700
from the start, Ma'am.

150
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,467
You're the one
causing harm here.

151
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:15,633
Sir, please...

152
00:08:15,767 --> 00:08:17,167
Sir.

153
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:19,133
Sir, please,
my child needs me.

154
00:08:19,267 --> 00:08:22,033
Please, let me leave.

155
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,033
Sir!

156
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:49,733
Mr. Cruz?

157
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:51,867
Doc, how's my daughter?

158
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,333
We did an urgent cranial
CT scan on your daughter.

159
00:08:55,500 --> 00:08:58,033
Luckily, there's no internal
bleeding.

160
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:00,000
And then we administered
medicines

161
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:03,133
to help reduce
the pressure on her brain.

162
00:09:03,267 --> 00:09:05,367
The swelling has started
to go down.

163
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:06,733
Is she out of danger now,
Doctor?

164
00:09:06,867 --> 00:09:09,300
That's something
we can't answer just yet.

165
00:09:09,433 --> 00:09:12,700
As you know,
the first 24 to 48 hours

166
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:14,067
are the most crucial.

167
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,767
We really need
to observe closely

168
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:21,200
for any delayed reactions
to her head trauma.

169
00:09:21,333 --> 00:09:22,933
That's just how it is.

170
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:24,133
I'll leave you here for now.

171
00:09:24,267 --> 00:09:25,333
Thank you, Doctor.

172
00:09:31,067 --> 00:09:34,100
Manuel, Jessica
will get better.

173
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,267
We just have to trust
and pray.

174
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,633
Let me out of here!

175
00:09:44,767 --> 00:09:45,833
My child needs me!

176
00:09:45,967 --> 00:09:47,567
Let me out of here!

177
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:49,900
You can't lock me up!

178
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:54,233
I need to see my child.

179
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:58,667
Take me to the hospital.

180
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:02,900
Jessica needs me.

181
00:10:03,067 --> 00:10:05,700
Jessica needs me!

182
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:08,433
<i>- Let go of me!
- That's enough!</i>

183
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:11,900
<i> Jessica!</i>

184
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:17,133
I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to do that.

185
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:24,800
I didn't...

186
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,667
I didn't mean it.

187
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:45,100
Dad, why don't you just
call Mommy Pretty?

188
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:48,400
Maybe not now, dear.

189
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:51,533
There are a lot of people there.
I'm sure they stopped Hazel.

190
00:10:51,667 --> 00:10:53,133
Please make sure
of that, Dad.

191
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:54,800
Please.

192
00:10:54,933 --> 00:10:58,167
Let's just see
if she's really okay.

193
00:10:58,300 --> 00:11:01,567
What are you staring at?

194
00:11:01,700 --> 00:11:03,533
I just don't want to
get involved in their problems.

195
00:11:03,667 --> 00:11:04,533
That's all.

196
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:07,100
Could you please put your pride
aside for now?

197
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:11,800
Mom, Dad, you two
might end up fighting.

198
00:11:11,967 --> 00:11:13,700
You're not supposed
to be enemies.

199
00:11:15,367 --> 00:11:16,333
Sorry, dear.

200
00:11:17,367 --> 00:11:18,767
Your mom's just
being persistent.

201
00:11:20,800 --> 00:11:23,967
Dad, Mom's right.

202
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:27,700
Instead of worrying here,

203
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,867
let's just check
on Mommy Pretty.

204
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:33,867
Mom, can you be the one to call?

205
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:47,867
I'll try calling
your Auntie Coleen.

206
00:11:51,433 --> 00:11:53,067
Hello, Coleen?

207
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,367
We're at the hospital, Daisy.

208
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:58,800
Jessica got hurt
when Hazel lost control.

209
00:11:58,933 --> 00:12:00,700
She's in the ICU now,
in critical condition.

210
00:12:02,100 --> 00:12:04,567
Coleen, how are you and Mom?
Are you okay?

211
00:12:04,700 --> 00:12:07,800
Mom and I are fine, Jeff.

212
00:12:07,933 --> 00:12:09,700
It's just Jessica
who's not.

213
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:11,933
Poor Auntie Jessica.

214
00:12:12,067 --> 00:12:14,067
I'll be praying for her,
Auntie Coleen.

215
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:15,800
Thank you, baby.

216
00:12:19,967 --> 00:12:21,033
Mom.

217
00:12:21,167 --> 00:12:23,067
- Yes?
- Jeff is asking how we are.

218
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,333
What?

219
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:25,500
<i> Let me talk to him, dear.</i>

220
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:29,333
Hello, Jeff?

221
00:12:32,167 --> 00:12:33,533
Come on, Jeff!

222
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:35,000
Why did you end the call?

223
00:12:35,133 --> 00:12:37,700
Your mom just wants
to talk to you.

224
00:12:37,833 --> 00:12:39,733
What for?

225
00:12:39,867 --> 00:12:40,933
I heard they're okay.

226
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,133
Mom.

227
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:50,533
It's okay, dear.

228
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:53,367
He still checked on us.

229
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,933
He's still
worried about us.

230
00:12:57,333 --> 00:12:58,533
By the way,
where's your dad?

231
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:05,733
Sir.

232
00:13:06,733 --> 00:13:09,633
Sir, please let me call
my lawyer.

233
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:11,433
That's my right.

234
00:13:11,567 --> 00:13:13,367
Bro, do we let her?

235
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,400
We were insulted
and sworn at earlier.

236
00:13:15,533 --> 00:13:17,100
And she even hurt us.

237
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:18,233
We have to, bro.

238
00:13:18,367 --> 00:13:19,667
She has that right.

239
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,600
Okay.

240
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:33,767
Thank you.

241
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,100
Please let me have my bag.

242
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:46,900
Thank you.

243
00:13:58,567 --> 00:14:00,533
Alice.

244
00:14:00,667 --> 00:14:03,700
Alice, please help me.

245
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:07,900
I'm being held here
at Dela Peña Police Station.

246
00:14:10,100 --> 00:14:12,000
Contact Attorney Salazar.

247
00:14:12,133 --> 00:14:13,100
Get me out of here.

248
00:14:13,233 --> 00:14:14,133
Please.

249
00:14:15,933 --> 00:14:17,500
Save the story for later!

250
00:14:17,633 --> 00:14:19,933
What's wrong with you?

251
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:23,633
Alice, please,
I need to get out of here.

252
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:26,800
I need to see Jessica
at the hospital, okay?

253
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:27,800
Please.

254
00:14:27,967 --> 00:14:29,867
Call Attorney Salazar.

255
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,667
All right, thank you.

256
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:35,367
Thank you.

257
00:14:43,133 --> 00:14:44,367
Manuel?

258
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:49,400
Thank you.

259
00:14:49,533 --> 00:14:51,267
Thank you
for coming to see me.

260
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,667
How's Jessica?

261
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,833
Jessica's safe, right?

262
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:57,700
Jessica's safe?

263
00:14:57,833 --> 00:15:00,400
My daughter's life is in danger
because of what you did!

264
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:13,467
Manuel...

265
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,933
Manuel, please...

266
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,700
Manuel, I didn't mean to.

267
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,033
She's my daughter...

268
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,500
Jessica is my daughter, too.

269
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,800
Manuel.

270
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:30,100
Manuel, please forgive me.

271
00:15:30,233 --> 00:15:31,967
Manuel, I didn't
mean to do that.

272
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:33,533
You're a monster, Hazel!

273
00:15:33,667 --> 00:15:35,100
- Monster!
- Stop it.

274
00:15:35,267 --> 00:15:36,500
- Sir!
- If anything bad happens

275
00:15:36,633 --> 00:15:39,600
to Jessica, I won't just charge
you with physical assault!

276
00:15:39,733 --> 00:15:41,267
It'll be murder
or homicide!

277
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:42,967
- You'll rot in jail!
- Let her go, Sir!

278
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,033
You monster!

279
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:45,033
Bro, that's enough!

280
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:47,667
- Stop!
- You're a monster, Hazel!

281
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:48,633
Monster!

282
00:15:48,767 --> 00:15:50,467
- Stop it.
- You're a monster, Hazel!

283
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:54,433
- Stop it, stop it.
- You'll rot in jail!

284
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:55,700
Jessica.

285
00:15:55,833 --> 00:15:57,100
Jessica!

286
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:00,533
I need to go to
the hospital!

287
00:16:00,667 --> 00:16:03,333
Sir! My daughter!

288
00:16:03,467 --> 00:16:04,900
Her life is in danger!

289
00:16:05,033 --> 00:16:07,433
No! Let me go, please!

290
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,067
Sir!

291
00:16:09,233 --> 00:16:10,100
- Get her inside.
- Manuel,

292
00:16:10,233 --> 00:16:11,300
I didn't mean to do that!

293
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:12,567
Manuel!

294
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:14,100
Please forgive me, Manuel!

295
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:16,333
- I didn't mean to!
- I love Jessica!

296
00:16:16,467 --> 00:16:19,233
- Get inside.
- I love Jessica!

297
00:16:19,367 --> 00:16:20,667
- Get inside.
- Wait!

298
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,367
My daughter!

299
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:24,467
My daughter is
in the hospital!

300
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,400
Wait! My daughter's life is in
danger!

301
00:16:27,533 --> 00:16:29,600
Wait!

302
00:16:29,733 --> 00:16:32,667
Wait, have mercy!

303
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,200
I didn't mean to do that!

304
00:16:36,767 --> 00:16:39,933
I didn't mean to do that!

305
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,833
Come on, Andrea. Why aren't you
picking up?

306
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:11,800
Andrea?

307
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,233
Andrea.

308
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:15,267
Andrea, wake up.

309
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,400
Andrea.

310
00:17:43,467 --> 00:17:44,533
Hey!

311
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:57,633
Jeff, why are
you still up?

312
00:17:57,767 --> 00:17:59,133
I've been calling Andrea.

313
00:17:59,267 --> 00:18:00,233
But she's not answering.

314
00:18:04,067 --> 00:18:06,000
Hello, Auntie.

315
00:18:06,133 --> 00:18:07,367
Auntie, have you
talked to Andrea?

316
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,967
Have you told her
what happened?

317
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:12,033
I sent her a text message.
But she didn't reply.

318
00:18:12,167 --> 00:18:13,967
She's probably sleeping.

319
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:15,133
<i> Why, Jeff?</i>

320
00:18:15,267 --> 00:18:17,767
She's not answering
my calls as well.

321
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:19,767
But this isn't her usual
sleeping time.

322
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:21,000
<i>All right, Auntie,
I'll just give her a call.</i>

323
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:23,200
Wait, wait. Aren't you going
to talk to your mom first?

324
00:18:31,467 --> 00:18:32,933
Daisy, I'm just going to
check on Andrea, okay?

325
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:34,433
Can you tell Tetay for me?

326
00:18:34,567 --> 00:18:36,033
What?

327
00:18:36,167 --> 00:18:37,300
It's already late.

328
00:18:37,433 --> 00:18:38,600
I know. I'm just worried.

329
00:18:38,733 --> 00:18:39,667
I can't sit still.

330
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:40,700
What if something already
happened to Andrea,

331
00:18:40,833 --> 00:18:42,633
and I don't even know?

332
00:18:42,767 --> 00:18:43,700
I have to go.

333
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:50,500
<i> This way, Attorney.</i>

334
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:53,800
Attorney.

335
00:18:53,933 --> 00:18:55,633
Thank you.

336
00:18:55,800 --> 00:18:57,167
Where's Alice?

337
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,233
She's on her way.

338
00:18:58,367 --> 00:18:59,633
Actually, she called me.

339
00:18:59,767 --> 00:19:00,933
That's why I came.

340
00:19:03,733 --> 00:19:05,167
Are we leaving now?

341
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,100
Are we going out?

342
00:19:08,233 --> 00:19:13,300
Mrs. Cruz, I'm sorry,
but it's Sunday.

343
00:19:13,433 --> 00:19:14,667
There's no office today.

344
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:17,233
There's no one available
to process your bail.

345
00:19:17,367 --> 00:19:21,400
The earliest we can do
that is tomorrow morning.

346
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:22,400
What do you mean?

347
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:25,033
This can't be, Attorney!

348
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:27,567
My daughter
is in the hospital.

349
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,900
Jessica's life is in danger.

350
00:19:29,067 --> 00:19:30,933
This can't wait!
I can't be stuck in here!

351
00:19:31,067 --> 00:19:32,433
Please, Attorney,
find a way.

352
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:33,567
I'm begging you.

353
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:35,533
Even if they have to cuff me,
I don't care.

354
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:38,033
Just let me see
my daughter.

355
00:19:38,167 --> 00:19:42,267
I'm really sorry,
but that's not how it works.

356
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:44,367
Attorney, this can't be.

357
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,900
Let me out of here!

358
00:19:48,033 --> 00:19:50,400
Don't you understand my
daughter's life is in danger?

359
00:19:50,533 --> 00:19:51,500
Please!

360
00:19:51,633 --> 00:19:52,533
Let me out!

361
00:19:52,667 --> 00:19:53,700
I need to be
with my daughter!

362
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,267
I need to see Jessica!

363
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:58,433
- Sir!
- Mrs. Cruz, that's enough.

364
00:19:58,567 --> 00:19:59,767
You might just make things
worse for yourself.

365
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,933
This could delay
your release even more.

366
00:20:03,633 --> 00:20:05,067
I can't stay locked up here,

367
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,400
not knowing what's happening
to my child!

368
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,800
I need to be with Jessica!

369
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:22,267
Only a demon
could do something like that

370
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:24,067
to her own child, Paz.

371
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:27,100
But you know what, friend?

372
00:20:27,233 --> 00:20:30,967
I can't really blame Hazel
for going crazy either.

373
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,233
Look, it's simple.

374
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:33,800
Just think about it.

375
00:20:33,933 --> 00:20:37,900
Her relationship with her family
is falling apart.

376
00:20:38,067 --> 00:20:38,967
Her whole family's
breaking down.

377
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:42,600
And then suddenly,
her family runs to you.

378
00:20:42,733 --> 00:20:46,600
Now, the three of you are
living under one roof.

379
00:20:46,733 --> 00:20:50,133
And let's not forget that
you and Manuel have history.

380
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:54,633
Not just history, you have
three children together.

381
00:20:54,767 --> 00:21:00,933
So any wife would
lose her mind.

382
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:03,000
I'm only helping Manuel.

383
00:21:04,267 --> 00:21:05,700
I know, friend.

384
00:21:05,833 --> 00:21:07,367
I know you are.

385
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:14,467
But honestly,
even if it weren't Hazel,

386
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:18,233
anyone else would still find
something wrong

387
00:21:18,367 --> 00:21:19,800
with your situation.

388
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:23,100
I'm not doing
anything wrong.

389
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:29,467
I'd never do to Hazel
what she did to me before.

390
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:32,233
I'm not a home wrecker.

391
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:34,900
Okay. Just make sure,
all right?

392
00:21:35,033 --> 00:21:37,300
Because I don't want what
Hazel's accusing you of

393
00:21:37,433 --> 00:21:39,133
to end up being true.

394
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:43,067
Sis, I don't want my BFF
to be the other woman.

395
00:21:45,133 --> 00:21:46,167
Manuel!

396
00:21:46,300 --> 00:21:49,400
Manuel, why did you go
to the precinct?

397
00:21:49,533 --> 00:21:50,433
Didn't I tell you?

398
00:21:50,567 --> 00:21:53,600
Atty. Yeban is already handling
the complaint.

399
00:21:53,733 --> 00:21:56,033
I just couldn't hold back
my anger toward Hazel.

400
00:21:56,167 --> 00:21:57,967
I had to let it out,
or I was going to explode.

401
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,767
Jessica!

402
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:16,167
- Call a doctor! Jessica!
- Jessica?

403
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:17,000
Jessica...

404
00:22:17,600 --> 00:22:18,833
- Dear! Coleen!
- Doctor!

405
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:21,600
Ask for help
from the nurse station!

406
00:22:21,733 --> 00:22:22,633
Jessica...

407
00:22:23,767 --> 00:22:25,000
Hurry up, dear!

408
00:22:25,133 --> 00:22:26,233
Doctor!

409
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:40,300
Sir?

410
00:22:40,433 --> 00:22:41,933
Sir, I'm begging you, please.

411
00:22:42,067 --> 00:22:46,567
Can you call my daughter
at the hospital?

412
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,533
Something bad
might've happened to her.

413
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,733
Please, sir, just check
how my daughter's doing.

414
00:22:50,867 --> 00:22:52,433
Please, I'm begging you.

415
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:54,533
Sir. Sir!

416
00:23:07,700 --> 00:23:10,567
What are you
staring at?

417
00:23:10,700 --> 00:23:12,633
What?

418
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:13,967
Just because you got here
before me,

419
00:23:14,100 --> 00:23:15,033
you think you can do something
to me?

420
00:23:16,467 --> 00:23:18,267
Are you going to hit me?

421
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,667
Try it!

422
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,067
Just try.

423
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:31,733
I don't know the whole story.

424
00:23:31,867 --> 00:23:34,433
But I get it.

425
00:23:35,633 --> 00:23:37,833
I'm a mother, too.

426
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,433
And I wouldn't be able
to sit still either

427
00:23:39,567 --> 00:23:42,033
if I didn't know
what was happening to my child.

428
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,233
What are you even
talking about?

429
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:56,700
Sir.

430
00:23:56,867 --> 00:23:59,300
Sir! Sir! Sir!

431
00:23:59,433 --> 00:24:02,200
Can you make just one call, Sir?

432
00:24:02,333 --> 00:24:04,133
Please.

433
00:24:04,267 --> 00:24:05,667
Just one call.

434
00:24:06,733 --> 00:24:09,633
Just one call.

435
00:24:09,767 --> 00:24:12,333
I just want to know...

436
00:24:13,367 --> 00:24:15,900
How is my child doing
in the hospital.

437
00:24:16,033 --> 00:24:17,700
Sir.

438
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:20,500
Just one phone call, sir.

439
00:24:20,633 --> 00:24:22,600
Sir!

440
00:24:22,733 --> 00:24:24,267
Sir, please!

441
00:24:27,300 --> 00:24:30,133
Sir, just one call.

442
00:24:31,533 --> 00:24:33,300
Just one call.

443
00:24:33,933 --> 00:24:35,933
Have mercy, please.

444
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:47,900
Andrea?

445
00:24:49,433 --> 00:24:50,333
Who are you?

446
00:24:50,467 --> 00:24:51,567
Bro, wait. Wait.

447
00:24:51,700 --> 00:24:54,233
- What did you do to Andrea?
- Wait!

448
00:24:54,367 --> 00:24:55,333
Hold on!

449
00:24:57,900 --> 00:24:59,433
Wait!

450
00:24:59,567 --> 00:25:00,600
I'm not doing anything wrong...

451
00:25:00,733 --> 00:25:02,500
What do you mean you're not
doing anything wrong?

452
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:03,667
Wait just a minute!

453
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,300
What do you mean you're not
doing anything wrong?

454
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:08,167
Jeff?

455
00:25:08,300 --> 00:25:09,867
Andrea?

456
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,400
Joel, what's going on?

457
00:25:11,533 --> 00:25:12,600
This jerk is taking
advantage of you!

458
00:25:12,733 --> 00:25:13,633
Andrea, no.

459
00:25:13,767 --> 00:25:15,233
That's not true!

460
00:25:15,367 --> 00:25:16,600
That's not true.

461
00:25:20,100 --> 00:25:21,567
Why am I wearing
different clothes now?

462
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:24,433
You, jerk!

463
00:25:24,567 --> 00:25:25,900
Ouch!

464
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,200
Which room is Jessica
Capistrano Cruz in?

465
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,133
She was brought here last night.

466
00:25:30,267 --> 00:25:32,233
I'm her mother, Hazel
Capistrano-Cruz.

467
00:25:32,367 --> 00:25:34,200
She's in the ICU, Ma'am.

468
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:35,433
Third floor.

469
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,933
I won't allow my daughter
to see the person who hurt her.

470
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:39,033
Come on!

471
00:25:39,167 --> 00:25:40,867
Hazel, just leave!

472
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,500
And if I don't leave,

473
00:25:42,633 --> 00:25:43,833
what are you going to do,
Manuel?

474
00:25:43,967 --> 00:25:46,433
- Let me go!
- Hazel, just go!

475
00:25:46,567 --> 00:25:47,967
Are you still angry
at your mother?

476
00:25:48,100 --> 00:25:49,433
This won't end, Joel,

477
00:25:49,567 --> 00:25:52,833
not until he kicks his ex
out of our house.

478
00:25:52,967 --> 00:25:56,933
Do you really have to go
with Manuel?

479
00:25:57,067 --> 00:25:59,900
Are you one of those people
casting suspicion?

480
00:26:00,033 --> 00:26:03,300
The way you and your ex behave,

481
00:26:03,433 --> 00:26:06,767
it's like you're already more
than just friends, isn't it?

482
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,133
We're just friends.

483
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:10,300
I'm the mother.

484
00:26:10,433 --> 00:26:12,367
But it's Felma
who's there.

485
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:14,133
We can't blame Manuel.

486
00:26:14,267 --> 00:26:17,267
Besides, you're the reason
Jessica got into that accident.

487
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:19,300
That accident
wouldn't have happened

488
00:26:19,433 --> 00:26:21,433
if Felma hadn't gotten involved.

489
00:26:21,567 --> 00:26:23,100
I need to see Jessica.

490
00:26:23,233 --> 00:26:24,800
I have to be near her.
